### ============================================================
### US-LEASE-01 → US-LEASE-06 — Lease lifecycle (landlord)
### ------------------------------------------------------------
### Prereq: run auth.http → login first so REST Client captures
### `accessToken` + `refreshToken`. Then run this file in the
### "local" (or "device") environment.
###
### ID chaining: this file logs in, fetches the landlord's first
### property, then its first room, so you do NOT need to hard-code
### roomId. US-TENANT-02 (tenant account provisioning) fires
### automatically when the lease is created.
### ============================================================

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### Log in as landlord (captures tokens — same pattern as auth.http)
### ------------------------------------------------------------
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### capture tokens
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.data.refreshToken}}

###

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### Helpers: resolve a room to lease against (US-LEASE-01 needs a
### room owned by this landlord). Fetch first property + first room.
### ------------------------------------------------------------
# @name firstProperty
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties?pageSize=2
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

@propertyId = {{firstProperty.response.body.data.[1].id}}

###

# @name firstRoom
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}/rooms?pageSize=1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###
@roomId = {{firstRoom.response.body.data.[0].id}}

###

### ============================================================
### US-LEASE-01 — Create a digital lease (tenant captured inline)
### Also triggers US-TENANT-02 (tenant account provisioning).
### Expect 201 { data: { lease:{...}, tenantAccountProvisioned:true } }
### Validation: end>start; no overlapping active lease for room;
### email/phone/idNumber format + uniqueness.
### ============================================================
# @name createLease
POST {{baseUrl}}/leases
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomId": "{{roomId}}",
  "tenant": {
    "fullName": "Tran Thi B",
    "phone": "0905556677",
    "idNumber": "07912304567",
    "email": "tkchi23@clc.fitus.edu.vn"
  },
  "startDate": "2026-07-01",
  "endDate": "2026-12-31",
  "agreedRent": 3500000,
  "deposit": 3500000
}

###
@leaseId = {{createLease.response.body.data.id}}
@tenantInfoId = {{createLease.response.body.data.tenantId}}

###

### Create with end-date before start-date (expect 422 UNPROCESSABLE)
POST {{baseUrl}}/leases
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomId": "{{roomId}}",
  "tenant": {
    "fullName": "Bad Lease",
    "phone": "0900000000",
    "idNumber": "0000000000",
    "email": "badlease@example.com"
  },
  "startDate": "2026-12-31",
  "endDate": "2026-07-01",
  "agreedRent": 1000000,
  "deposit": 1000000
}

###

### Create overlapping lease for the same room (expect 409 CONFLICT)
POST {{baseUrl}}/leases
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomId": "{{roomId}}",
  "tenant": {
    "fullName": "Overlap Tenant",
    "phone": "0907778889",
    "idNumber": "0799999999",
    "email": "overlap@example.com"
  },
  "startDate": "2026-08-01",
  "endDate": "2026-09-30",
  "agreedRent": 3000000,
  "deposit": 3000000
}

###

### ============================================================
### US-LEASE-02 — View lease information (landlord)
### Expect 200 { data: { ... room, tenant, period, status } }
### ============================================================
# @name getLease
GET {{baseUrl}}/leases/{{leaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ============================================================
### US-LEASE-02 — List leases (landlord sees all in portfolio)
### Expect 200 paginated; the created lease appears in `data`.
### ============================================================
# @name listLeases
GET {{baseUrl}}/leases
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ============================================================
### US-LEASE-03 — Update or renew a lease
### (a) Plain edit: change endDate / agreedRent / deposit
### Expect 200 with updated values.
### ============================================================
# @name updateLease
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/leases/{{leaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "endDate": "2027-01-31",
  "agreedRent": 3600000,
  "deposit": 3600000
}

###

### (b) Renewal: end current + create a new Active lease
### Expect 200 with a new lease id for the renewed period.
### (Run only after the plain edit above if you want a clean sequence.)
# @name renew
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/leases/{{leaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "renewalStartDate": "2027-02-01",
  "renewalEndDate": "2027-07-31",
  "agreedRent": 3700000,
  "deposit": 3700000
}

###

### Update a non-Active lease (expect 422 UNPROCESSABLE)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/leases/{{leaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agreedRent": -5
}

###

### ============================================================
### US-LEASE-06 — View upcoming lease expirations
### Expect 200 { data: [ { leaseId, propertyName, roomName,
### tenantFullName, endDate } ] } for the configured window.
### ============================================================
# @name upcoming
GET {{baseUrl}}/leases/upcoming-expirations
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ============================================================
### US-LEASE-05 — Lease-expiration reminder config (per property)
### GET current config, then enable 7/3/1-day reminders.
### Expect 200; enabled flags reflected in response.
### ============================================================
# @name getReminderConfig
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}/lease-reminder-config
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

# @name setReminderConfig
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}/lease-reminder-config
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "remindAt30Days": true,
  "remindAt15Days": true,
  "remindAt7Days": true
}

###

### ============================================================
### US-LEASE-04 — End a lease and release the room
### Expect 200 with status "Ended" + actualEndDate set.
### After this, the room shows Vacant (derived) and history is kept.
### ============================================================
# @name endLease
POST {{baseUrl}}/leases/{{leaseId}}/end
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "actualEndDate": "2027-03-31"
}

###

### End again (expect 422 UNPROCESSABLE — only Active can be ended)
POST {{baseUrl}}/leases/{{leaseId}}/end
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "actualEndDate": "2027-02-01"
}

###

### ============================================================
### US-TENANT-02 + US-AUTH-05 — Tenant provisioned by US-LEASE-01
### can now log in (username = phone) with the emailed TEMP password
### and MUST change it before other actions. Replace {{tempPassword}}
### with the emailed value to exercise the tenant flow.
@tempPassword =91c34620d9fa7f31b8
### ============================================================
# @name tenantLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "0905556677",
  "password": "{{{{tempPassword}}}}"
}

###
@tenantAccessToken = {{tenantLogin.response.body.data.accessToken}}

### Tenant views their own lease (US-LEASE-02, tenant scope)
GET {{baseUrl}}/leases/{{leaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tenantAccessToken}}

### Tenant must change temp password (US-AUTH-05)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{tenantAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "{{tempPassword}}",
  "newPassword": "NewTenant123",
  "newPasswordConfirmation": "NewTenant123"
}

###
